headline: Arista Networks (ANET) Q2 Revenue Surges To US$2.2 Billion
summary: Arista Networks (ANET) recently delivered impressive second-quarter results, with revenue and net income surging year-over-year, prompting a 59% stock price rise over the last quarter. The company reported revenue of $2.2 billion and net income of $888 million, spurring an uplift in its annual growth projections by 25% for 2025. This growth is reinforced by the launch of AI-driven products and an acquisition in the SD-WAN space. These developments come amid a broader bullish trend in tech...
